This is an experimental HAL component for LinuxCNC3.

It covers the aspect of monitoring HAL pins for changes, and generating a
status update message if so.

* Required packages for ubuntu 12.04:
    sudo apt-get install \
            libzmq-dev libprotobuf-c0-dev protobuf-c-compiler \
            python-protobuf.socketrpc python-protobuf protobuf-compiler \
            libprotoc-dev libprotobuf-dev
    install czmq from https://github.com/zeromq/czmq
    install pyzmq from https://github.com/zeromq/pyzmq

* Required packages for Debian squeeze
  apt-get install libprotobuf-c0-dev  libprotobuf-c0 \
	  protobuf-c-compiler libprotobuf-dev libprotobuf6 \
	  libprotoc-dev protobuf-compiler  python-protobuf \
	  libtool python-setuptools cython

  install libzmq from https://github.com/zeromq/libzmq
  install czmq from https://github.com/zeromq/czmq

  install pyzmq with:
     easy_install pyzmq

* To resolve "Failed to remake makefile `Makefile'" for *pb* include files:
    touch hal/halreport/*.proto # renew file timestamps
    make # to generate protocol-buf files


To run the application:

- in a window, start
  $ halcmd -f periodic-example.hal

- in a second window, start
  $ gladevcp -u zmqdemo.py zmqdemo.ui

(see zmqdemo.py variable dest for addressing, as well as halreport.ini)